NAME		reply
SYNTAX		reply [message]
DESCRIPTION	Reply to the person who last told you something.
		If message is omitted, you will be prompted for the message
		and your current reply list will be used in the reply.
		This latter option is very useful if you a receiving a lot
		of tells and your reply list is likely to have changed before
		you have finished typing the command.

		If message begins with a : character, then the reply is sent
		as a 'remote'
		If message begins with a . character, then the reply is sent
		as a 'feeling'
SEE ALSO	tell, remote
